lecture: systems that persist

why do you keep rebuilding the same thing?

you find something that works
you lose it
you rebuild it
it’s not quite the same

again and again

this is not a tooling problem
this is a system problem

most ai workflows are not systems
they are moments

prompt → output → gone

there is no memory
there is no lineage
there is no persistence

so the cost of progress is:

rebuild everything
every time

that does not scale

a real system does something different

it remembers how it worked

you don’t just get the output
you get the method

and once you have the method:

you can run it again
you can change one variable
you can improve it

this is the difference between:

playing with ai
and
building with ai

